Bloomberg News Wins a Record 23 SABEW Awards for 2010

-- B y  
-- 
2011-03-23T15:17:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/bloomberg-news-wins-a-record-23-sabew-awards-for-2010.html
                                
Press Release  Society of American Business Editors and Writers Honors
Bloomberg in Every Category of Journalism  New York -- Bloomberg News has won 23 Society of American
Business Editors and Writers Awards for 2010, more than any
other news organization this year.  Bloomberg won in every
category of journalism for its investigative, explanatory,
feature, breaking news and opinion coverage of companies,
markets and the economy.  The winning stories were recognized as they appeared in
Bloomberg Markets magazine, Bloomberg News, Bloomberg
Businessweek and on Bloomberg Television.  “As SABEW represents the best and brightest of our peers in
journalism, we are most grateful and honored to receive the
recognition these awards confer,” said  Matthew Winkler , Editor-
in-Chief of Bloomberg News.  Today’s announcement brings the overall total number of SABEW
awards for Bloomberg News to 70, which was recognized for 6
awards in 2009. Since its inception in 1990, Bloomberg News has
won more than 500 awards. The awards will be presented on
Saturday, April 9, at the 48th annual conference in  Dallas .  The full list of awards Bloomberg won are online at:
 http://sabew.org/2011/03/168-winners-announced-for-sabew ’s-
annual-best-in-business-awards/  About Bloomberg  Bloomberg is the world’s most trusted source of information for
financial professionals and businesses.  Bloomberg combines
innovative technology with unmatched analytics, data, news, and
display and distribution capabilities, to deliver critical
information via the Bloomberg Professional service and
multimedia platforms.  Bloomberg’s media properties span
television, radio, digital and print, making up one of the
world’s largest news organizations with more than 2,300 news and
multimedia professionals at 146 bureaus in 72 countries.  Bloomberg Contact  Meghan Womack, +1 212-617-8514,  mwomack4@bloomberg.net 
